 After computing the European option prices with the Heston model at given expiry dates and strike prices,
 these option prices were inverted via the Black-Scholes' model to produce a volatility surface using the 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

{
\backslash
it Brent}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 method.
 Since the Heston model sometimes leads to call option prices that are outside of the price range of the Black-Scholes' model,
 a curve-fitting algorithm was applied to yield a smooth curve for each slice of the surface.
\end_layout

