 I fitted the Ornstein-Uhlenbeck (OU) process to the historical values of a portfolio of stock indices.
 I received the portfolio compositions from the strategists and calculated the historical values of the portfolio from the historical values of the stock indices.
 Then the OU process was fitted by regressing the price increments onto the prices,
 with a constant term included.
 The parameters of the fitted process were used as an input to algorithmic trading signal generation.
